---
hvy_version: 0.1
template: true
title: Resume
reader_max_width: 60rem
ai-context: This is a resume document. Use the top-skills-tools-technologies
  section for featured reference cards only; the skills, tools-technologies, and
  languages sidebar sections are the main reusable libraries for detailed
  reference records. History and education have body sections with structured
  component-lists for expandable record rows. Projects, publications, awards,
  and certifications are section templates that should be added only when
  source-backed content exists. Keep dated main-section records in reverse
  chronological order with newest entries first. History should use one
  expandable record per organization when roles are contiguous; put promotions,
  title changes, or adjacent date ranges at the same organization inside that
  single expanded record instead of creating duplicate organization rows. Use
  the tableform History section flavor for longer histories with more items, and
  the linear History section flavor for shorter histories. One project,
  publication, certification, degree, skill, or tool should usually be
  represented as one expandable reusable record. Local skills/tools lists inside
  history, project, publication, certification, award, and education records are
  supporting references and should not be treated as the main libraries.
ai-import-guidance: During resume import, map source-backed awards into the
  Awards section template even when the source mentions awards inside work
  history, projects, education, summaries, or other prose instead of providing
  an explicit Awards heading. Treat those mentions as award-record items when
  they identify a distinct award, recognition, honor, finalist placement, prize,
  or equivalent accolade. Do not create Awards when the source has no distinct
  source-backed award-like item. Any sort of job goes under professional
  history. A skill is something you do. For example, programming. A tool /
  technology is something you use and would have experience with. Such as a
  programming language, machinery, etc. The Languages section is only for human
  languages someone can speak, read, write, or otherwise communicate in.
  Programming languages are tools / technologies, not Languages section entries.
importPreplan:
  - - header
    - summary
    - locations
  - - skills
    - tools-technologies
    - languages
    - top-skills-tools-technologies
  - - history
    - resume-awards
  - - resume-projects
    - resume-publications
  - - resume-certifications
    - education
  - - languages
    - resume-section
section_defaults:
  css: "margin: 0.5rem 0;"
text_line_styles:
  panel-heading:
    label: Panel heading
    css: "margin: 0 0 0.25rem;"
  section-heading:
    label: Section heading
    css: "margin: 0.5rem 0 0.25rem;"
  detail-heading:
    label: Detail heading
    css: "margin: 0.4rem 0 0.1rem;"
  detail-body:
    label: Detail body
    css: "margin: 0 0 0.35rem; margin-left: 0.5rem;"
theme:
  colors:
    --hvy-bg: rgb(40, 40, 45)
    --hvy-bg-alt: rgb(24, 80, 48)
    --hvy-surface: "#31383d"
    --hvy-surface-alt: "#3a484b"
    --hvy-surface-tint: rgba(58, 72, 75, .38)
    --hvy-text: "#e0e0e0"
    --hvy-text-alt: "#ffffff"
    --hvy-text-muted: "#dedede"
    --hvy-link-color: "#e0e0e0"
    --hvy-link-hover-color: "#ffff99"
    --hvy-accent-1: rgb(14, 160, 56)
    --hvy-accent-1-alt: "#10ca45"
    --hvy-accent-1-text: "#f0f0f0"
    --hvy-accent-2: rgb(16, 241, 141)
    --hvy-accent-2-alt: "#37c871"
    --hvy-button-bg: "#1b6949"
    --hvy-button-hover-bg: rgba(0, 255, 200, .6)
    --hvy-button-text: "#f0f0f0"
    --hvy-button-hover-text: "#ffff99"
    --hvy-highlight-1: rgba(0, 255, 0, .1)
    --hvy-highlight-2: rgba(229, 233, 0, .25)
    --hvy-border: "#c0c0c0"
    --hvy-border-alt: "#ffffff"
    --hvy-border-input: "#ffffff"
    --hvy-border-translucent: rgba(255, 255, 255, .2)
    --hvy-xref-card-bg: "#3a484b"
    --hvy-xref-card-hover-bg: rgba(0, 255, 200, .6)
    --hvy-table-header: rgb(40, 40, 45)
    --hvy-table-row-bg-1: "#3a484b"
    --hvy-table-row-bg-2: "#31383d"
    --hvy-icon-muted: rgba(224, 224, 224, .42)
    --hvy-focus: "#10ca45"
    --hvy-focus-ring: rgba(16, 202, 69, .68)
    --hvy-focus-glow: rgba(0, 255, 200, .3)
    --hvy-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, .2)
    --hvy-shadow-md: rgba(0, 0, 0, .5)
    --hvy-shadow-lg: rgba(0, 0, 0, .7)
    --hvy-overlay: rgba(0, 0, 0, .55)
    --hvy-danger: rgb(139, 0, 0)
    --hvy-warning: "#e5e900"
    --hvy-warning-bg: rgba(229, 233, 0, .16)
    --hvy-warning-border: "#ffdb58"
    --hvy-warning-text: "#e5e900"
    --hvy-success: "#50c878"
    --hvy-success-bg: rgba(16, 245, 75, .2)
    --hvy-success-border: "#37c871"
    --hvy-code-bg: "#101011"
    --hvy-code-text: "#e0e0e0"
    --hvy-code-muted: "#b0b0b0"
    --hvy-code-string: "#ffff99"
    --hvy-code-builtin: rgb(16, 241, 141)
    --hvy-code-keyword: "#10ca45"
    --hvy-code-function: "#50c878"
    --hvy-code-number: "#79c0ff"
