<!--hvy: {"id":"header","lock":true,"expanded":true,"highlight":false,"contained":false,"priority":true,"description":"Resume identity header","hideIfUnmodified":true}-->
#! Info

 <!--hvy:text {"id":"resume-name","align":"center","css":"margin-bottom: 0;"}-->
  # James Glynn Hutchison

 <!--hvy:text {"id":"resume-pronunciation","align":"center","css":"margin-top: 0;","visibleScript":"name = doc.component.get_text(\"resume-name\").replace(\"#\", \"\").strip()\nreturn len(name) > 0 and \"<!-- value\" not in name"}-->
  [James Glynn Hutchison]

 <!--hvy:button {"id":"generate-pronunciation-button","editorOnly":true,"buttonVisibleScript":"name = doc.component.get_text(\"resume-name\").replace(\"#\", \"\").strip()\npronunciation = doc.component.get_text(\"resume-pronunciation\").replace(\"[\", \"\").replace(\"]\", \"\").replace(\"<!-- value {\\\"placeholder\\\":\\\"pronunciation\\\"} -->\", \"\").strip()\nreturn len(name) > 0 and \"<!-- value\" not in name and len(pronunciation) == 0","buttonSourceScript":"name = doc.component.get_text(\"resume-name\").replace(\"#\", \"\").strip()\nif \"<!-- value\" in name:\n    return \"\"\nreturn name","buttonPrompt":"Generate a concise pronunciation guide for this resume name. Return only the pronunciation text, using simple uppercase/lowercase syllables and hyphens. Do not include brackets, labels, or explanation.","buttonTargetScript":"clean = response.strip()\nif clean.startswith(\"[\") and clean.endswith(\"]\"):\n    clean = clean[1:-1].strip()\ndoc.component.set_text(\"resume-pronunciation\", \"[\" + clean + \"]\")","buttonInputCharLimit":400,"buttonOutputCharLimit":120,"buttonPositionTargetId":"resume-pronunciation","buttonCss":"position: absolute; top: 50%; right: calc(50% + 3.75rem); transform: translateY(-50%); transform-origin: right center; padding: 0.04rem; --hvy-button-content-padding: 0.1rem 0.28rem; --hvy-button-font-size: 0.68rem;"}-->

 <!--hvy:text {"id":"info-placeholder","align":"center","css":"margin: 0.5rem 0; margin-top: 1rem;","fillIn":true}-->
  title
<!--hvy: {"id":"summary","lock":false,"expanded":true,"highlight":false}-->
#! Summary

 <!--hvy:expandable {"lock":true}-->
  <!--hvy:expandable:stub {}-->

   <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin-bottom: 0;"}-->
    # Summary

   <!--hvy:text {"id":"summary-add-a-short-professional-summary-and-elaborate-in-the-expanded-section","css":"margin-top: 0;","placeholder":"Add a short professional summary and elaborate in the expanded section"}-->

  <!--hvy:expandable:content {}-->

   <!--hvy:text {"css":"margin: 0;"}-->
    Experience leading a team in a SCRUM environment.
    Broad background of technologies, tools, and skills.
    BS Computer Science.
    Developer with over 16 years industry and Python experience.
    Most recently used languages: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, Scala.
    Other languages: C# .NET, PHP, Perl, C/C++.
    Database experience: PostgreSQL, BigQuery.
    Elasticsearch experience.
    Google Cloud Platform (GCP) experience.
    Building services in App Engine standard and flex.
    Cloud Tasks, PubSub, Cron, Datastore, Dataflow, Kubernetes, Stackdriver monitoring and alerts.
    AI experience: LLMs, LangChain, SuperAGI, OpenAI integrations, running quantized Code Llama Instruct locally.
    Misc. AWS experience.
    Web services development and distributed system architecture, weighted towards middle/backend but capable and familiar with common front-end patterns and tools.
    CI/CD experience: CircleCI, TravisCI, and some GitLab.
    Experience leading efforts to improve developer experience by evaluating developer pain points through surveys, first-hand experience, and interviews, then identifying and creating solutions.
    Maintained dev containers at Carta and built tooling to reduce onboarding time to minutes.
    Maintained and trained developers on using DevSpace at Carta.
    History of exceeding expectations, ramping up quickly, excelling at position, and rarely behind.
    Bias towards action, pragmatic development practices, prioritizing risk management, and not creating unnecessary work.
    Bias towards creating business value and going where needed.
    Open to managing.
